{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "6682bd78ba0e94a3c4025cd9", "type": "numerical", "level": 3, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": 210, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "", "questionLabels": [], "question": {"text": "Suppose a uniformly charged wall provides a uniform electric field of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>\u00d7</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>4</mn></msup><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><mo>\u00a0</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math> normally. A charged particle of mass <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></math> being suspended through a silk thread of length <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>20</mn><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi>cm</mi></math> and remain stayed at a distance of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi>cm</mi></math> from the wall. Then the charge on the particle will be\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi></msqrt></mfrac><mi>\u03bc</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math> where\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo></math>\u00a0________ [use <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>\u00a0</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math>]", "image": null}, "options": [], "correctValue": "3", "solution": {"text": "<p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/6d1fe597-09ec-49b4-804f-91d9d341ee8c.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 228px;\"/></p><p>As we can see from geometry,\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mi>\u03b8</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>10</mn><mn>20</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>\u21d2</mo><mi>\u03b8</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>30</mn><mo>\u00b0</mo></math></p><p>Vertical component of tension will balance the weight and the horizontal component will balance the electric force. Therefore,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mi>\u03b8</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>q</mi><mi>E</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>\u21d2</mo><mi>tan</mi><mn>30</mn><mo>\u00b0</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>q</mi><mo>\u00d7</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>\u00d7</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>4</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>\u00d7</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mo>\u00d7</mo><mn>10</mn></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>\u21d2</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>q</mi><mo>\u00d7</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>6</mn></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>\u21d2</mo><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mfrac><mo>\u00d7</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></msup><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mfrac><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi>\u03bcC</mi></math></p><p>Hence,\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math>.</p>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "bucket": "Tough Ques (JEE Adv)", "concepts": [], "masterId": "MOGJMPYQ45098914", "subject": "Physics", "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eb9a"], "topics": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "65c4c0c11d30997d3436bb07", "title": "JEE Main 2024 (01 Feb Shift 2)", "is